1)check_email function:
Accepts an email string
Uses a regular expression to check the format
Outputs “valid” and returns 0 on successful match
Outputs “invalid” and returns 1 on error
2)check_phone function:
Accepts a phone number string
Checks the format: +1(123)-456-78-90
Outputs “valid” and returns 0 on successful match
Outputs “invalid” and returns 1 on error
3)check_input function:
Accepts the check type (email/phone) and value
Calls the appropriate checking function
Returns error code 2 for an invalid option
